{{spanish name|López|Mora}}
'''Hernán Rodrigo López Mora''' (born on 21 January 1978 in [[Montevideo]]) is an [[Uruguay]]an [[Association football|football]] player who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Club Atlético Banfield]] of the [[Primera División Argentina]].

==Career==
===Club===

López began his career with [[Club Atlético River Plate (Uruguay)|River Plate de Montevideo]] in [[Uruguay]]. He had short stints with [[Torino FC]] of Italy and [[AO Kavala]] of Greece in 1998 with along compatriot [[Pablo Gaglianone]]. In 2000 he joined [[Colo-Colo]] of Chile.

He returned to Uruguay in 2001 to play for [[Danubio FC]] and in 2002 he joined [[Racing Club de Montevideo]]

Between 2002 and 2004 he enjoyed a successful stint with [[Club Olimpia|Olimpia]] of [[Paraguay]] where he was part of the team that won both [[Copa Libertadores]] [[Copa Libertadores 2002|2002]] and [[Recopa Sudamericana]] [[Recopa Sudamericana|2003]].

In 2004 he joined Mexican side [[Pachuca CF]] but after only a few games he returned to Paraguay to play for [[Club Libertad|Libertad]] where he scored an impressive 39 goals in 71 league games, won the [[Paraguayan Primera División|Primera División]] championship in 2006 and finished as the topscorer.

López returned to Mexican football in 2008 joining [[Club América]] where he played alongside a number of other South American players such as [[Federico Insúa]] of Argentina and [[Salvador Cabañas]].<ref>[http://southamerican-futbol.blogspot.com/2011/03/federico-insua-gambeta-vs-tecos.html Federico Insúa gambeta vs Tecos]</ref> He had a successful time with América, scoring a famous hat-trick against Tecos in the 2007 Apertura<ref>[http://southamerican-futbol.blogspot.com/2011/03/rodrigo-lopez-golazo-vs-tecos-apertura.html Rodrigo López golazo vs Tecos]</ref> and helping the team to win the 2008 [[InterLiga]].

In 2008 he joined [[Argentina|Argentine]] [[Club Atlético Vélez Sársfield|Vélez Sársfield]] and had an unsuccessful start with the team, quickly reverted by contributing 11 goals in their championship season of [[Primera División Argentina 2008–09#Torneo Clausura|Clausura 2009]].<ref>[http://www.26noticias.com.ar/hernan-rodrigo-lopez-desde-tierras-uruguayas-llego-el-gran-goleador-92207.html 26 Minutos]. Retrieved December 22, 2009. {{es icon}}</ref>

López was bought by Argentine side [[Estudiantes de La Plata]] in June 2010 for a fee of around $750,000 US dollars.<ref>{{cite news|title=Con Rorro y el Torito |newspaper=Olé |date=2010-06-26 |url=http://www.ole.com.ar/estudiantes/Rorro-Torito_0_287371326.html |language=Spanish |accessdate=2010-06-27}}</ref> He scored a number of vital goals for the club in his first season helping the club to win the [[2010–11_Argentine_Primera_División_season#Torneo_Apertura|Apertura 2010]] tournament. He scored his first hat-trick for Estudiantes with three headers in a 5-1 win against Paraguayan side Guaraní in the group stages of the [[2011 Copa Libertadores]].<ref>[http://southamerican-futbol.blogspot.com/2011/03/rodrigo-lopez-golazo-conta-guarani.html Rodrigo López vs Guaraní]</ref> In the following game he scored the winning goal against league leaders Racing Club.<ref>[http://southamerican-futbol.blogspot.com/2011/03/hernan-rodrigo-lopez-vs-racing-clausura.html Hernán Rodrigo López vs Racing, Clausura 2011]</ref>

On July 2011, he signed a 2 year contract with [[Club Atlético Banfield]].

===National team===

On the youth level, López was runner-up with [[Uruguay national under-20 football team|Uruguay U-20]] at the [[1997 FIFA World Youth Championship]]. He even played the final against [[Argentina national under-20 football team|Argentina]].

López played a friendly match for [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] against [[China national football team|China]] in 1996.<ref name="Ole">[http://www.ole.clarin.com/notas/2009/08/21/futbolinternacional/01982936.html "La Celeste (y blanca)"] ''Olé''. Retrieved August 21, 2009. {{es icon}}</ref> Thirteen years later, in 2009, he was called again by coach [[Oscar Washington Tabárez]] for a friendly match against [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] and for the World Cup qualifying games against [[Peru national football team|Peru]] and [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]].<ref name="Ole"/> He was also part of the squad that achieved the qualification by defeating [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]] on the playoff. However, he was not part of the Uruguayan squad that played the World Cup.

On July 27, 2010 he was reserved to play a friendly match against  [[Angola national football team|Angola]] in [[Lisboa]] .

